{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780129880975,"sessionID":"ses_18801b231ffe1T23Rry15kpUZw","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_00_A9XuqKrpa8FxXiOllqh42602","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/deepseek/state-parts/iter-004.jsonl","content":"{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":4,\"model\":\"deepseek\",\"newInfoRatio\":0.6,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"iter4\"}\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/deepseek/state-parts/iter-004.jsonl","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/deepseek/state-parts/iter-004.jsonl","time":{"start":1780129880967,"end":1780129880973}},"id":"prt_e78025514001ROInT3khWwa0Y6","sessionID":"ses_18801b231ffe1T23Rry15kpUZw","messageID":"msg_e780243b6001evVv9r9IwgwCIz"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780129902267,"sessionID":"ses_18801b231ffe1T23Rry15kpUZw","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_01_ndcveE0zkdgjT3KmMyLU5791","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/deepseek/deltas/iter-004.jsonl","content":"{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":4,\"model\":\"deepseek\",\"newInfoRatio\":0.6,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"iter4\"}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i4-01\",\"label\":\"Report shape — three layers (machine JSON + human markdown + dashboard card) mirroring Lane B's report.json pattern with an added human-readable narrative. JSON is primary artifact; markdown derives from same data; dashboard provides at-a-glance monitoring.\",\"iteration\":4}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i4-02\",\"label\":\"Machine JSON schema (report.json) — 5 top-level sections: metadata (skill slug/path, executor, scoringMethod), dimensions (D1a/D1b/D2/D3/D4/D5 with raw/normalized/weighted/variance fields), composite (overallScore, utilizationRate, utilizationMatrix, variance), bottlenecks (ranked Remediation[]), and scenarios (full per-scenario detail + skillOffBaseline).\",\"iteration\":4}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i4-03\",\"label\":\"Scoring rollup — three-stage aggregation: Stage 1 per-scenario sub-scores (D1a binary, D1b post-hoc set-membership, D2 hitRate × (1-fpPenalty), D3 inverse tool-call count, D4 LLM-as-judge delta, D5 static connectivity). Stage 2 per-dimension mean + variance across scenarios. Stage 3 weighted-sum composite (0-100). All intermediate scores preserved for audit.\",\"iteration\":4}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i4-04\",\"label\":\"Confirmed dimension weights — D1a=0.15, D1b=0.15, D2=0.20, D3=0.15, D4=0.25, D5=0.10. Grounded in Lane A's existing 5-dimension weights and iteration-001 recommendations. D1 routing = 0.30 total, D4 usefulness = highest single weight.\",\"iteration\":4}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i4-05\",\"label\":\"Remediation taxonomy — 10 categories (MISSING_TRIGGER, AMBIGUOUS_TRIGGER, DEAD_INTENT_KEY, ORPHANED_RESOURCE, BROKEN_PATH, OVER_LOADING, UNDER_LOADING, CONFUSION_NEAR_NEIGHBOR, TOO_BROAD_INTENT, MISSING_NEGATIVE_GUIDANCE). Each maps to a concrete file-level change. Each entry carries estimatedImpact, targetFile, action, changeDescription, difficulty, and verification for direct Lane A consumption.\",\"iteration\":4}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i4-06\",\"label\":\"Bottleneck ranking algorithm — estimatedImpact = (1 - dimScore.normalized) × dimWeight × affectedScenarioCount. Favors high-weight dimensions with widespread impact. Severity thresholds: CRITICAL = D1a<20, HIGH = score<50 or >50%affected, MEDIUM = 50-69, LOW = 70-89. Scores>=90 generate no findings.\",\"iteration\":4}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i4-07\",\"label\":\"Human markdown report skeleton — 10-section structure modeled after sk-doc benchmark report template + Llama 3 evaluation methodology. Sections: Executive Summary, Dimension Radar, Utilization Matrix, Routing Health, Resource Discovery, Efficiency, Usefulness, Structural Health, Ranked Bottlenecks, Methodology Notes. Pass/Fail thresholds: PASS >=80 no CRITICAL, NEEDS_IMPROVEMENT 50-79 or HIGH, CRITICAL <50.\",\"iteration\":4}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i4-08\",\"label\":\"Dashboard integration — reducer gains optional skillBenchmarkReports key in experiment-registry.json with per-skill composite scores, statuses, top bottlenecks, utilization rate, and scenario summary. Follows existing graceful-degradation pattern (missing → null).\",\"iteration\":4}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i4-09\",\"label\":\"Prior art — Dynabench (Kiela et al. 2021) principle that benchmarks must produce actionable insights, not just aggregate accuracy, directly informs Lane C's remediation-first report design. Llama 3 evaluation methodology provides structural template for multi-category drill-down with failure taxonomy + concrete recommendations.\",\"iteration\":4}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i4-10\",\"label\":\"Lane C → Lane A hand-off contract — each remediation entry is structured as a Lane A candidate (targetFile + action + changeDescription + verification), enabling pipeline: diagnose → improve → verify. Remediation entries carry difficulty rating (TRIVIAL/EASY/MODERATE/HARD) for triage.\",\"iteration\":4}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i4-11\",\"label\":\"Negative scenario scoring — D1a scores 100 when advisor correctly does NOT recommend the target skill (precision measure). Negative scenarios excluded from D1b/D2/D3/D4 to avoid false-penalizing skills for correctly not loading resources when they should not be invoked.\",\"iteration\":4}\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/deepseek/deltas/iter-004.jsonl","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/deepseek/deltas/iter-004.jsonl","time":{"start":1780129902257,"end":1780129902264}},"id":"prt_e78025bc8001aIwJ6VzC47j8hQ","sessionID":"ses_18801b231ffe1T23Rry15kpUZw","messageID":"msg_e780243b6001evVv9r9IwgwCIz"}}
